5000|$|The {{portability}} of <b>social</b> <b>security</b> {{benefits is}} the ability of workers to preserve, maintain, and transfer acquired <b>social</b> <b>security</b> rights and <b>social</b> <b>security</b> rights {{in the process of being}} acquired from one private, occupational, or public <b>social</b> <b>security</b> scheme to another. <b>Social</b> <b>security</b> rights refer to rights stemming from pension schemes (old age, survivor, disability), unemployment insurance, health insurance, workers' compensation, and sickness benefits.|$|R
